  "license_terms": "Iranian government legal text (public law); hosted for research use by Iran Data Portal, cite Iran Data Portal + original law",
  "notes": "39 files: one file per fiscal year (SH calendar, filename = year, e.g. 1371.pdf = FY1371) plus several files with descriptive names for the same/adjacent years where the portal hosts a bill, amendment, or law variant separately (e.g. 1399-Bill.pdf, 1400-Bill-part-I/II.pdf, LAW-1400.pdf, law-1399.pdf, Law-1398.pdf, budget1398-1.pdf, Budget-1396-1.pdf, Budget-Law-1396.pdf, Budget-1397.pdf, Budget-1401-2022-2023-Bill.pdf, AMENDMENT.pdf, Eblagh097.pdf [notification/ promulgation text]). provincial-data-budget.xlsx is the only structured/tabular file, covering provincial budget allocations 1996-2014 per the page's own description. Filenames are exactly as served by the source (mixed case/format is original, not normalized by the agent).",
  "failures": [],
  "extraction_method": "Extracted 2026-07-13 into data/processed/iran_plan_budget_org_series/annual_budget_law_totals_1371_1401.csv (125 rows, 30 of 31 possible fiscal years FY1371-1401). Method: for PDFs with a clean font/CMap, pdftotext -layout + NFKC-normalized keyword search for the law's own 'ماده واحده' (single-article) clause; for scanned or mojibake-encoded PDFs (most of this folder), pdftoppm -r 300-400 page render + direct visual reading of the PNG, cross-checking the parenthetical digit string against the spelled-out Persian number words (one file, 1400-Bill-part-I.pdf, had garbled numeral glyphs specifically -- words were used as primary source there instead). Every multi-component total was checked for internal consistency (do the parts sum to the stated whole?); mismatches were kept as printed, never reconciled. Full page-by-page working log: logs/downloads/iran-plan-budget-org-extraction.log. Full provenance/caveats: data/processed/iran_plan_budget_org_series/README.md.",
  "extracted_to": "data/processed/iran_plan_budget_org_series/annual_budget_law_totals_1371_1401.csv"
